wikipedia_page.main: John Francis O'Driscoll (20 September 1921 in Cork, Ireland – 11 March 1988 in Swansea, Wales), commonly referred to as Jackie O'Driscoll, is a former  Irish footballer who played as a winger for several teams in the League of Ireland. He also played for Swansea Town. O'Driscoll was a dual international and played for both Ireland teams - the FAI XI and the IFA XI.
